        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 17 at 9:24AM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>At 924 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Stratford, or 14 miles northeast of Little Falls, moving northeast at
50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Northville, Caroga Lake, Tenantville, Pinnacle, Blackbridge,
Lotville, Whitehouse, Knappville, Maple Grove, Fical Corners,
Carpenters Corners, Caroga Lake Public Campground, Tomantown,
Scotchbrush, Phipps Corners, Arietta, West Day, Hope Falls,
Wheelerville, and Bleecker Center.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
